values: [Warning: 84 images and foul language] || [ 1.0 ] When we left off last time, the Zenk shack home, owned by legacy founder Alfred Zenk and his girlfriend Daisy, was about to be invaded by a nefarious and severely ugly burglar... OH SHIT, HE IS GOING TO STEAL ALFRED'S PRECIOUS TOILET OR SHOWER? :O No, he went outside and stole the warm-up bar. :| Whatever. LOL. :O Daisy: Come quick! There's a burglar and...OH CRAP, HE'S STANDING RIGHT NEXT TO ME. Alfred: NOT THE BOOKSHELF! NOOOOOOO. Poor little knowledge sim. I'll never get tired of that face. GET IN MY UGLACY, STAT. He's so proud of his haul. And Daisy doesn't seem to care at all. o_O YOU'RE TAKING YOUR TIME, MISS POLICEWOMAN. Daisy and Alfred: HEY, WHERE DID OUR STUFF GO? Policewoman: LOL, sorry, I messed up. :D Alfred: >:[ Cleaning the shower soothes his tortured soul. Look at his joy. Alfred: That's right, little sponge. Wash away all of my anger. Alfred: Ahh, all better. Alfred: NO, WAIT. I miss my stuff! They miss the warm-up bar. BUT I REPLACED IT WITH A STATIONARY BICYCLE. IT'S BETTER, GUYS. Alfred also misses the chess set that the buglar stole. EVEN THOUGH I REPLACED THAT, TOO. WTF, pay attention. That want always makes me amused. But wait... HIS NAME IS RUSS BEAR? Hahaha. He's too charming for words. Alfred: I know what'll raise my spirits! ...Stop it already. Finally, I snag Alfred an entertainment job, so it's time to get some charisma points. LOL. Around this point, I realized who Alfred reminds me of. ...TOURETTES GUY. (NSFW!) Alfred: BALLS! That's a snazzy outfit. :D Daisy comes home from work and makes the acquaintance of Miranda Hobbes. And they argue about hats. And just out of the blue *COUGH*, the burglar appears! Daisy: I'll teach you to steal my stuff! This family has anger management issues. :D YAY, ENEMIES! Annnnnnnd the harrassment begins. Russ stole an invisible newspaper. Honestly? Who cares--the Zenks never read the paper anyway. Alfred: I love when you beat up people. BABY MAKING TIEM! :D >:| Daisy: HEY, HONEY, YOU LIKE BABIES RIGHT? Alfred: ...Wait. Why? T_T Oh, yeah, Daisy -never- gets morning sickness. But she does clog up the toilet. Which pisses off Alfred, who throws a fit whenever I make him fix things. Alfred would LOVE if she got morning sickness. Alfred: Oh, porcelain friend, you're as dear to me as the shower and...oh yeah, my girlfriend. ....??? They gain hobby points in their sleep? Alfred: Oh, yeah, here's the shiny, since you're kind of carrying my spawn. Daisy: YEEEEEEE! :D Daisy: Just what I've always wanted! Getting married in my pajamas. Russ Bear returns to knock over the trash can again, so Daisy runs out to confront him... Daisy: RAWWWWWWR. >:O Daisy: DO NOT MESS WITH A PREGNANT LADY. Oh that he would leave them alone... Bzzzzump! :D Daisy thinks about how badass she is while she's on the pot. :P LOL! When Alfred returns from work, he notices a change. Alfred: The house didn't look like this when I left this morning. WTF? Alfred: What a piece of crap this new house is. >:| But look, I built you a master bathroom...WITH FLOORS AND WALLS AND EVERYTHING. Alfred: Well, ok, I DO LIKE THIS. :D ENJOY THE BATHTUB WHILE YOU CAN, BUDDY. It's gonna be sold for a crib! BZZZZUMP #2! DON'T BE REPULSED BY THE MESS. YOU MADE IT. >:[ Alfred: AWWWW CRAP. MORE CHARISMA POINTS? Alfred: I HATE DOGS. Alfred: BUT I STILL LOVE MY TOILET. <3 If it weren't for woohoo, the Zenks would probably dead or more insane. I'm not even joking about that. Alfred: RAGGHHH. I DON'T WANT TO FIX THE COMPUTER. I LOVE HIM SO MUCH. Alfred, look how happy you are while fixing it! ...Maybe not? Daisy: Sooooo, now that we're hitched... Daisy: I totally own your balls. Alfred: UGHHHH, I HATE THISSSSS. Daisy: HAY, REMEMBER I'M PREGNANT! But....You don't look it. Daisy: BUT I REALLY, REALLY AM. I just didn't put on weight! Daisy: HURGGHGHHHHHH! Alfred: Look at me! LOOK AT HOW BUFF I AM! :D The baby's named Augusta. Because Augusta Zenk sounds cool. What...? Alfred: Damn, she's hot now that she popped that kid out. Ok, bye! Daisy: I'm going to hover over my sleeping husband and think about how hot he is instead of going to work! Yeah, the nanny is shit. What else is new? I've a feeling that Augusta is going to spend most of her young life with stink fumes coming out of her. The nanny...didn't leave until about midnight, even though Alfred came home hours ago. Then at some point, Alfred got really, really pissed off. His fun and social levels were in the red and he wouldn't do anything. Alfred: LOOK AT HOW ANGRY I AM. Why are you angry? Alfred: I DON'T KNOW. BUT I'M SUPER PISSED OFF. Alfred: MAYBE IT'S BECAUSE I GOT ROBBED A COUPLE MONTHS AGO. Ok...? Will you go play Sims 3? Alfred: I guess. >:[ Alfred: BOOM! BOOM! PSSSSFFFFFT BOOM! I didn't know grouchy sims make bomb sounds when they play Sims 3...? It was funny, though! SEXY TIME!
Death's fears crack me up: I sort of want to make sure that wherever my first sim dies that there're vermin around to freak out ol' Grimmy. ;)
